  <section class="kindle-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="kindle-container">
      <div class="kindle-section-header">
        <h2 class="kindle-section-title">Kindle & Fire Tablet Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="kindle-section-subtitle">Common questions about Kindle and Fire repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="kindle-faq-list">
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you replace a cracked E-Ink screen on my Kindle in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — we replace damaged E-Ink electrophoretic displays on most Kindle e-reader models including Kindle Paperwhite, Oasis, Scribe, and standard Kindle generations. E-Ink screens require model-specific replacement modules — contact us to confirm availability for your specific Kindle before visiting.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does a Kindle battery replacement take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Most Kindle battery replacements are completed within 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Kindle e-reader batteries are designed to last weeks between charges — if yours is dying in hours, a battery replacement can fully restore that extended reading life.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>My Fire tablet won't charge. Can you fix it in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — Fire tablet charging port failures are one of our most common repairs, especially on devices used by children where ports get debris pushed in. We clean the port first before recommending replacement — most Fire tablet charging port repairs are completed same-day.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair older Kindle models in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">We service most current Kindle and Fire generations — parts availability varies for older discontinued models. Contact us with your specific model name and generation so we can confirm whether we have parts in stock before your visit.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Will I lose my books and content after Kindle or Fire repair?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">No — your Amazon account content including books, magazines, apps, and settings is stored in the cloud and will automatically sync back to your repaired device. Data loss is rarely a concern for Kindle and Fire repairs since everything is tied to your Amazon account.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Is it worth repairing my Kindle or should I buy a new one?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">It depends on the model and repair needed — a battery replacement on any Kindle almost always makes financial sense, while an E-Ink screen replacement on an older Kindle may approach the cost of a new entry-level model. We always give you an honest comparison before starting so you can make an informed decision.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Fire HD Kids tablets in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all Fire Kids Edition tablets including Fire HD 8 Kids, Fire HD 10 Kids, and Fire 7 Kids. Kids Edition devices have rubber protective cases that help with drops, but the internal screens still crack — we repair all Kids Edition models at our Winnipeg location.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a Kindle that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — a Kindle that won't power on is usually caused by a fully depleted battery, a software hang, or a charging port fault. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know exactly what the issue is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Fire Max 11 tablets in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — we repair the Fire Max 11 including screen, battery, and charging port repairs at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. The Fire Max 11 is Amazon's largest and most premium tablet — contact us to confirm current parts availability for your specific repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="kindle-faq-item">
          <summary class="kindle-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Kindle and Fire tablets in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="kindle-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="kindle-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts Kindle and Fire tablet repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For E-Ink screen repairs or less common models, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

